# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — Coding Values

What code this project welcomes and rejects. Agents read this before writing;
reviewers judge against it. `AGENTS.md` carries the short version loaded every
turn — this is the full reference, read on demand.

Defaults below match the project's anti-slop stance. The owner can override any —
when they do, log it as a decision (`Lxx` in `docs/architecture/decision_log.md`)
and update this file. An agent that disagrees with a value raises it; it does not
quietly ignore it. Fill the `<...>` slots from the real stack + domain; delete
sections that don't apply yet, add project-specific ones as they emerge.

## Vision

Code reads like the architecture says it works. Open a file → see its
responsibility, its data, its failure path. No hidden state, no lifecycle spread
across the codebase, no clever indirection. Stable > fast.

## Stack

Filled from the chosen stack; the *why* per choice lives in `decision_log.md`
